    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1910-07-19T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1910-07-19T00:00:00-05:00" n="758"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d758">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 212.11G16/17.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Ambassador <persName type="from">Wilson</persName> to the
                            <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">American Embassy</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Mexico</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1910-07-19">
                            <hi rend="italic">July 19, 1910</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I have the honor to acknowledge the receipt
                    to-day of the department’s No. 74, of the 12th instant,<note n="1"
                        xml:id="d758fn1">Not printed.</note> inclosing the papers in the extradition
                    case of Heliodoro Garcia, charged with assault with intent to commit murder in
                    the State of California.</p>
                <p>These papers have to-day been presented to the department for foreign affairs,
                    and the extradition of the fugitive has been requested in accordance with treaty
                    stipulations. In case extradition is granted Mr. Cervantes will be promptly
                    advised.</p>
                <p>I have, etc.,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Henry Lane Wilson.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
